The package netgen.tar.gz in this directory (if present) is a CVS checkout 
of netgen's repository at 27. Feb 2008, containing the files needed to build
nglib (for license, see netgen/LGPL).

If the package is not present, you can obtain the relevant files by performing
an CVS checkout from Netgen's repository. Follow the instructions on netgen's
we site:

     http://www.hpfem.jku.at/netgen/

In order to build a shared object of nglib for Mesh3D, you will have to:

- unzip the package: tar xvfz netgen.tar.gz (or CVS checkout)
- Copy the file COofMP.cpp in netgen/ngcore
- Copy the file makedll.sh in netgen/ngcore
- Copy the file testmain.cpp in netgen/ngcore
- Edit the file netgen/libsrc/interface/nglib.h by removing the comments in:

// #ifdef __cplusplus
// extern "C" 
// {
// #endif

// #ifdef __cplusplus
//  }
// #endif

- cd to netgen/ngcore and run the script "makedll.sh"

- test the lib as:

 g++ testmain.cpp
 ./a cube.surf

- copy ngcore/libng.dll and libsrc/interface/nglib.h in Mesh3D's main dir.

